  "title": "Rotation-tolerant representations elucidate the time course of high-level object processing",
  "description": "This dataset comprises electroencephalography (EEG) recordings from 16 participants viewing object images presented at eight different 2-D rotations in rapid visual streams at two presentation rates (5 Hz and 20 Hz). The study investigates rotation-tolerant neural representations and their temporal dynamics during high-level object processing, providing insights into how the visual system encodes object identity invariant to viewpoint changes.",
  "methods_description": "EEG recordings were collected from 16 participants viewing object images presented in eight different 2-D rotations. Stimuli were displayed in rapid visual streams at two presentation rates: 5 Hz and 20 Hz. Data are provided in standard BIDS format.",
